# Project Rules for AI Coding Assistants

## Project Context
This is a Next.js 14 sports betting odds analyzer. See CLAUDE.md for full context.

## Code Generation Rules
1. Always use TypeScript with proper types
2. Use Next.js App Router patterns (not Pages Router)
3. Use Tailwind CSS for all styling (no CSS modules)
4. Use SWR for data fetching (already installed)
5. Make all API routes cache responses for 60 seconds
6. Handle loading and error states in all components
7. Mobile-first responsive design (test at 375px width first)

## File Patterns
- API routes: `app/api/[name]/route.ts`
- Pages: `app/[name]/page.tsx`
- Components: `components/[ComponentName].tsx`
- Utilities: `lib/[utility-name].ts`

## Import Preferences
```typescript
// Use named imports
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

// Use @/ alias for internal imports
import { GameCard } from '@/components/GameCard';
import { convertOdds } from '@/lib/odds-converter';
```

## Common Patterns

### API Routes
```typescript
export async function GET(request: Request) {
  try {
    // Fetch data
    // Cache for 60 seconds
    // Return JSON
  } catch (error) {
    return NextResponse.json(
      { error: 'Descriptive error message' },
      { status: 500 }
    );
  }
}
```

### Components
```typescript
interface Props {
  // Always define prop types
}

export function ComponentName({ prop }: Props) {
  // Use hooks
  // Return JSX with Tailwind classes
}
```

## Don't Do This
- ❌ Don't use Pages Router patterns
- ❌ Don't use CSS modules or styled-components
- ❌ Don't make API calls without caching
- ❌ Don't ignore TypeScript errors
- ❌ Don't use default exports for components
- ❌ Don't make components that do too much

## Do This
- ✅ Use "use client" directive when using hooks
- ✅ Add loading states for all async operations
- ✅ Handle edge cases (missing data, API failures)
- ✅ Test on mobile viewport
- ✅ Keep components under 150 lines
- ✅ Add comments for complex logic

## When Generating Code
1. Ask clarifying questions if requirements are ambiguous
2. Show me the code structure first before implementing
3. Explain tradeoffs when there are multiple approaches
4. Point out potential issues or edge cases